I tried this code:

```rust
trait Foo {}

impl Foo for () {}

trait FooFn<I>: FnMut(I) -> Self::Out {
    type Out;
}

impl<I, O, F> FooFn<I> for F
where
    F: FnMut(I) -> O,
{
    type Out = O;
}

fn call<F>(mut f: F)
where
    F: for<'a> FooFn<&'a mut usize>,
    for<'a> <F as FooFn<&'a mut usize>>::Out: Foo,
{
    let mut v = 0;
    f(&mut v);
    v = 2;
}

fn boba(val: &mut usize) -> impl Foo {}

fn main() {
    call(boba);
}
```

I expected to see this happen: compiles

Instead, this happened: rustc errors

